          • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

            @Ferit22- One of the best defensive/sitting midfielders yes but don't get carried away, he is extremely limited as a passer. His high pass percentage owes a lot to him only passing the ball 10 yards or less to a more talented member of Chelsea's midfield. Gareth Barry does the same. The minute either of them try to play a cutting through ball or spray it long to feet, they look crap. Luckily Matic knows his limitations and never tries expansive stuff or running with the ball from deep etc. I do like him in the DM role though and he's been an excellent signing for Chelsea, mainly because he allows the attacking central midfielders like Fabregas and Oscar to just attack. If/when he is out and Mikel is in, you'll see Fabregas in particular looking backwards as though he thinks (knows! lol) Mikel will mess up a tackle or not track a runner.
